:INFO
Safety and Permitting for Small Wind Turbines
Key safety considerations and permitting requirements before installing a small wind turbine at home or off-grid property.

:CHECKLIST
Safety and Permitting Checklist
[ ] Check local zoning laws for tower height restrictions
[ ] Verify setback requirements from property lines and structures
[ ] Apply for a building permit if tower exceeds local height limits
[ ] Notify your utility if grid-tied or if required by local code
[ ] Conduct a soil test before setting tower foundation
[ ] Use rated guy wire and turnbuckles for all tower anchors
[ ] Install an overspeed protection or furling system on the turbine
[ ] Include a dump load resistor bank to protect batteries from overcharge
[ ] Add a manual disconnect switch accessible from ground level
[ ] Inspect all guy wire anchors and tower hardware annually

:NOTE
Never work on a turbine tower alone. Always have a second person present when raising, lowering, or servicing the tower. Use a safety harness rated for climbing work if you ascend the tower for any reason.
